They met together in Galilee. And Jesus said to them, "The Son of Man is going to be delivered into the hands of men."
"They will kill him, and on the third day he will rise again." The disciples were greatly distressed.
Jesus and his disciples arrived at Capernaum. And there the tax collectors came to Peter and asked him, "Does your teacher not pay the temple tax?"
He answered, "Yes, he does." When Peter came into the house, Jesus spoke first. "What do you think, Simon?" he asked. "Who collects taxes from the kings of the earth? From their sons or from strangers?"
Peter replied, "From strangers." Jesus said to him, "Then the children do not need to pay."
But we don't want to anger them. Go to the lake and cast your line. Take the first fish you catch. Open its mouth. You will find there the very coin you need. Take it and give it to them as a tax for me and you.
